<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12148b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12148b">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12148b"> 148(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> a bishop &mdash; eat capons</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">On m&apos;a racont&eacute; l&apos;histoire d&apos;un pr&ecirc;tre, brave homme d&apos;ailleurs, qui avait tout fait, lui et sa famille, pour obtenir l&apos;&eacute;piscopat. On lui demande: Avez-vous ambitionn&eacute; cette charge. &mdash; Bien s&ucirc;r, tout le monde le sait bien. &mdash; Voulez-vous r&eacute;pondre &agrave; Dieu des ouailles qui vous seront confi&eacute;s? &mdash; Ah! Mais non. &mdash; Dites que oui. &mdash; Non, non, mille fois non, et il se d&eacute;mit disant: Je croyais qu&apos;&ecirc;tre &eacute;v&ecirc;que consistait &agrave; manger du poulet tous les jours. <br><font color="green">[I was told the story of a priest, a good man who had done everything, he and his family, to become bishop. He was asked: &mdash; Do you want this appointment. &mdash; Of course, everybody knows. &mdash; Will you answer to God for the flock that will be entrusted to you. &mdash; Oh, no. &mdash; Say yes. &mdash; No, no, a thousand times no, and he resigned saying: <mark>I thought that being a bishop means eating chicken every day</mark>.]</font> <small> Matthieu-Maxime Gorce, <a name="STVF" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#STVF"><cite title="source">Saint Vincent Ferrier</cite></a> (1924) 155</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
